<HEADLINE>
FT  07 OCT 93 / Changes to collection of national insurance recommended
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE RULES for income tax and national insurance contributions should be
brought closer together to cut the costs to business, a government working
group said yesterday.
The group from the business community, whose report was published yesterday
by Mr Peter Lilley, the social security secretary, said the two systems
should use the same definitions of earnings and expenses, and the
Contributions Agency should use the administrative arrangements used by the
Inland Revenue.
The group also recommended a variety of ways to change the collection of
national insurance. Mr Lilley has yet to decide which aspects of the report
to adopt.
</TEXT>
