<HEADLINE>
FT  07 OCT 93 / Shetland salmon farmers to get compensation for Braer
contaminated fish
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SHETLAND SALMON farmers are to be paid Pounds 14m compensation for fish
still contaminated by the Braer oil tanker disaster.
One million year-old salmon will be destroyed after the farmers argued
successfully that they could still cause health problems.
One quarter of Shetland's salmon was contaminated by the spill last January.
Until this settlement, the International Oil Pollution Compensation fund had
been paying compensation to farmers on a month-by-month basis in the belief
the fish would clean themselves as they grew.
</TEXT>
