<HEADLINE>
FT  06 OCT 93 / London Stock Exchange: BAe easier
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOEL KIBAZO, CHRISTOPHER PRICE, SAQIB QURESHI and CHRISTINE BUCKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in British Aerospace (BAe) fell sharply as doubts about its proposed
regional jets joint venture with Taiwan resurfaced following a renewed
attack on the deal by the country's opposition political party.
Opposition deputies were reported to have suggested that the Taiwan
Government may drop its support for the proposed Pounds 250m venture. The
reports once again led to jitters on the London market which saw the shares
tumble 13 to 407p at the day's worst, before they steadied, assisted by the
strong market trend, to close 9 off at 411p, in thin trading of 1.6m.
One analyst said: 'There is nothing concrete or new in these doubts but it
brings to the surface worries that the deal may yet fail.'
