<HEADLINE>
FT  06 OCT 93 / London Stock Exchange: Renewed pressure on BAT
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOEL KIBAZO, CHRISTOPHER PRICE, SAQIB QURESHI and CHRISTINE BUCKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE downward slide in tobacco and financial services group BAT Industries
continued yesterday after Hoare Govett and SG Warburg joined the list of
houses that has recently downgraded profit expectations at the group.
Active selling of the stock brought volume of 9.4m by the close as the
shares ended 5 off at 456p, having touched 450p earlier in the day.
Hoare Govett was said to have moved its current year forecast from Pounds
1.86bn to Pounds 1.80bn citing pressure on the US domestic tobacco market
and in international exports for the move.
Researchers at Warburg are believed now to be expecting current year profits
of Pounds 1.8bn against a previous estimate of Pounds 1.828bn. The group
reported profits of Pounds 1.65bn last year.
Shares in BAT fell sharply at the end of last week after UK analysts on a
visit to the group's US insurance operations came away with a less than rosy
picture of near term trading.
