<HEADLINE>
FT  06 OCT 93 / World Stock Markets: Strategists plump for Pacific Rim
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PACIFIC RIM equity markets, already attracting US analysts, continue to win
converts.
The global strategy team at Nomura in London has doubled its model portfolio
weighting for Hong Kong to 6 per cent and is introducing Malaysia with 3 per
cent and the Philippines and Korea with 2 per cent each.
The re-rating, at the expense of the US, doubles Nomura's total weighting
for emerging markets to 20 per cent.
Mr Nicholas Knight, who heads the Nomura team, said that the attractions
were growth rates which look outstandingly good by western standards, and
generally reasonable market valuations.
Mr David Roche of Morgan Stanley, which again raised its Hong Kong weighting
yesterday, suggested that one outcome of events in Moscow could be
convergence between Russia and China if an authoritarian, pro-reform
government was installed. He advised building equity weightings in the Far
East, particularly connected to the China story, at the expense of Europe.
</TEXT>
