<HEADLINE>
FT  06 OCT 93 / International Company News: Hershey chairman to quit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANK MCGURTY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
HERSHEY Foods, the US chocolate producer, said yesterday that Mr Richard
Zimmerman would step down as chairman and chief executive at the end of the
year, writes Frank McGurty.
Mr Kenneth Wolfe, currently president and chief operating officer, was
elected by the board of directors as his successor. Mr Joseph Viviano,
president of Hershey Chocolate USA, will replace Mr Wolfe.
'These changes have been studied by the board over the past two years and
are part of a planned, orderly succession,' said Mr Zimmerman, who has
headed the Pennsylvania-based company since 1985.
Hershey, which expects record earnings this year in spite of an overall
slump in domestic candy sales, recently launched a white chocolate version
of its Kisses candy. The new product, Hugs, is expected to generate annual
sales of Dollars 100m.
