as a governor in the British public prison service before joining UK
Detention Services.
Although there are currently only two privately run prisons, the government
is committed to extending private management to about 10 per cent of the
system. Potential private sector operators are strengthening their
management teams with experienced recruits from the public sector and
overseas.
