FT  06 OCT 93 / Portsmouth Port may be in jeopardy
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Portsmouth's municipal ferry port says it could be in jeopardy if the
government refuses its request to borrow Pounds 7m for expansion. The port
needs to reclaim land, improve facilities and increase berths for the new
super-ferries if business is not to be lost to other ports and the Channel
tunnel. The improvements would cost Pounds 20m by the end of the decade and
Pounds 7m in the financial year 1994-95. Because the port is owned by
Portsmouth district council it is subject to constraints on local government
spending and cannot borrow funds without government approval.
