FT  06 OCT 93 / Ulster talks
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR James Molyneaux, the Ulster Unionist leader, yesterday said that the
Hume-Adams political initiative was designed to wreck hopes of Northern
Ireland having its own government.
As SDLP leader Mr John Hume prepares to brief the Irish government on
