   By ANDREW BAXTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
GIBSON GROUP, the Glasgow-based power-plant contractor, has reached
preliminary agreement to supply a 120MW power station to Liaoning province
in China.
Final negotiations will start in the next few weeks on the contract, which
would be worth about Pounds 65m.
The group's main contracting company, Gibson Wells Engineering, has been
working on the project for the past three years.
The company is also discussing further contracts in China for power stations
ranging from 100MW to 700MW. It said it expected to reach agreement soon
with 'a substantial US company' which was looking to invest in power
projects in China.
