<HEADLINE>
FT  05 OCT 93 / London Stock Exchange: Gas trails
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOEL KIBAZO, CHRISTOPHER PRICE and SAQIB QURESHI
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in British Gas trailed the market closing a penny lower at 325 1/2 p,
following volume of 5.9m, after analysts at Nomura urged investors to sell
the stock.
The new oils and gas team at the securities house believe the outlook for
the stock remains uncertain as 'it looks increasingly unlikely that the
government will accept the recent Monopolies and Mergers Commission report
on the break up of British Gas.'
Sentiment was further dented by news from the company that it expects its
share of the firm contract gas supply market to drop to 55 per cent by the
end of next year from its current level of around 68 per cent.
